   The capacity audience -- invited friends, relatives and theatrical personalities as well as 850 members of the public who started lining up at 7 a.m. -- heard recollections of an energetic Bernstein who danced until dawn in discos as well as a poignant account of his final days. Marilyn Horne closed the program with "Somewhere," the emotional anthem from "West Side Story," after which Laurents directed the audience's attention to the large photo that hung over the stage: an exuberant 39-year-old Bernstein, nearly levitating outside the theater where "West Side Story" had opened in Washington .
